Yaws - Papua New Guinea (New Britain) 20010906.2133
Date: 7 Sep 2001 07:07:32 +0200
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON <http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Some background data on yaws in Papua New Guinea
--------------------------------------------------
Yaws has been a reportable disease in this country since 1969. High
activity is present in East New Britain, Karkar Island, New Ireland, North
Solomon, Milne Bay, Madang, East Sepik, and West Sepik.
Milne Bay reported 54 cases (Samarai Island) in 1935; one during 1974 to
1979. A resurgence of cases occurred in Madang (Kar Kar Island) and Milne
Bay (North Kiriwina Island) during the 1980's.
2063 cases were reported nationwide in 1988; 3421 in 1989; 4170 in 1991. A
large outbreak was reported in New Ireland during 1998 to 1999.
--
Stephen Berger, MD
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
